The paper deals with the use of deep learning-based solutions for automatic image annotation in the field of surgical data science. The paper proposes a self-supervised learning approach that uses unlabeled video data to learn a representation of the target domain that boosts the performance of machine learning algorithms. This approach is likely to fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
